    "sections": {
      "PURPOSE": "3/2 Sniper Section trains to ensure Soldiers can effectively engage targets ranging from 300m to 1200m.",
      "MISSION": "3/2CR Sniper Section conducts MK22 and M2010 zero, data collection, and qualification IOT ensure Sniper Section is qualified on their weapon systems and ready for future operations.",
      "END STATE": "SMs are proficient and qualified on each sniper weapon systems. Concept of the Operation: This OPN will be conducted in III Phases:\nPhase I (Planning & Prep): Begins with identifying personnel to be trained and provide range support and ends when Sniper Section SP to Range 109 NLT 200630JUL23.",
      "KEY TASKS": "100% accountability of MWE, police call range, range cleared, ammo pickup, and safe movement back to RB.\nService & Support: Class I: A-M-A\nClass V: 1000 Rounds A191 – 300/900 Rounds AA11\nMedical Support: PLT Medics Ammo DO – 200800JUL23/Ammo PU - 211430JUL23",
      "EXECUTION": "): Begins when personnel SP to Range 109 and ends when training is complete NLT 211500JUL23.",
      "COMMAND AND SIGNAL": "PACE Plan\nP: 163 (TSM)\nA: 163 (SINGARS)\nC: ATAK (HNC) E: Signal\nSupporting",
      "TASKS": "Engage Targets with an M107 and M2010 TC 3-22.10\nZero an M107, M2010 TC 3-22.10\nLoad an M107, M2010 TC 3-22.10\nConcurrent Training Plan:\n- Observe Shooting while not firing IOT train wind calls and corrections\nUniform: IAW Dragoon Standard, Slick when firing\n05JUL23\n10JUL23\n11JUL23\n20-21JUL23\nTBD\n1. Plan the Training\n2. Train/Certify Leader\n3. Recon Training Site\n4. Issue the OPORD\n5. Rehearsal\n6. Exec. the Training\n7. Conduct an AAR\n8. Retrain/Retry\n12JUL23\n21JUL23\n06JUL23\nN\nPersonnel Required: 1x OIC, 1x RSO, 1x Gate Guard, 2x Safeties, 1x Medic, 1x MEV Driver, 1x Ammo NCO, 2x Ammo Detail\nEquipment Required: 1x Range Box, 10x zero targets, 12x Iron Maidens, 1x Target Stand, 8 hard targets and vehicles\nTimeline: 20JUL23\n0630 – SP Troop\n0730 – Arrive at Range/Occupy\n0800 – Ammo Drop\n0830 – Safety Brief\n0900 – Range Wet\n1800 – Range Dry\n2045 – Night Safety Brief\n2130 – Range Wet\n2300 – Range Dry\nRG109 Sniper Range CONOP\n21JUL23\n0830 – Safety Brief\n0900 – Range Wet\n1400 – Range Dry\n1430 – Ammo Pick-up\nNLT 1500 – Range Clear\nFigure 1. Range 109 complex.\nFigure 2. Range 109 in GTA."
    },
